Wrapper for AORSF (Oblique Random Survival Forest)

Source: R/surv.aorsf.R
surv.aorsf.Rd

Final Production Wrapper for AORSF (Tunable & Robust).

Usage

surv.aorsf(
  time,
  event,
  X,
  newX,
  new.times,
  obsWeights,
  id,
  n_tree = 500,
  leaf_min_events = 5,
  mtry = NULL,
  ...
)

Arguments

time

Observed follow-up time; i.e. minimum of the event and censoring times.

event

Observed event indicator; i.e, whether the follow-up time corresponds to an event or censoring.

X

Training covariate data.frame.

newX

Test covariate data.frame to use for prediction. Should have the same variable names and structure as X.

new.times

Times at which to obtain the predicted survivals.

obsWeights

Observation weights.

id

Optional cluster/individual ID indicator.

n_tree

Number of trees to grow (default: 500).

leaf_min_events

Minimum number of events in a leaf node (default: 5).

mtry

Number of predictors evaluated at each node.

...

Additional arguments passed to orsf.

Value

A list containing:

  • fit: The fitted model object (e.g., the raw coxph or xgb.Booster object). If the model fails to fit, this may be an object of class try-error.

  • pred: A numeric matrix of cross-validated survival predictions evaluated at the specified new.times grid.
